cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.DL, cs.MM, cs.HC 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image analysis and binarization. It may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it involves processing historical documents and manuscripts. Deep learning (cs.DL) could also be a relevant sub-category as many recent advances in image analysis have been achieved through deep learning techniques. Multimedia (cs.MM) could also be a possible sub-category as the paper deals with processing images. Finally, human-computer interaction (cs.HC) could be a relevant sub-category as the paper deals with evaluating the performance of algorithms on historical documents, which may have implications for user interfaces and accessibility.
